content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 1211.26 - Any article referenced to this section

State Regulations
(a) Any article listed in section
1211.150
and referenced to this
section may or may not be a compressed gas. When it is not identified by the
prescribed D.O.T. caution label for dangerous articles and is known not to meet
the description of a dangerous article, the article is allowed passage provided
the shipping order, bill of lading, or other shipping paper shows the following
certification: "This shipment conforms to Port Authority of New York
and New Jersey rules for the transportation of explosives and other dangerous
articles via its tunnels, the G.W.B. Lower Level and G.W.B. Expressway."
